==English==
===Verb===
'''jerryrig''' (''past tense: jerryrigged'')
#To assemble a [[mechanical]] or electrical device in a [[hasty]], low-quality manner, especially when cheap, low-quality, or inapproprate materials are used.
#To assemble a mechanical or electrical device in a fundamentally [[unsafe]] manner, usually in such a way that the device is doomed to failure.
#To fix a mechanical or electrical device in the above manners.

==== Usage note ====
The word ''jerryrig'' only applies to mechanical or electrical devices. Inanimate objects built in the above manner are said to by [[jerrybuild|jerrybuilt]].

